所以，这就是你在这些条件句中的用法。

162
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:55,960
If I were you, or if you were president of the United States.
“If I were you”，或者“if you were president of the United States”。

163
00:07:55,960 --> 00:07:57,360
Yeah, this is a rule.
是的，这是一个规则。

164
00:07:57,360 --> 00:07:58,640
So this is a grammar rule.
所以，这是一个语法规则。

165
00:07:58,640 --> 00:08:02,120
We're not going to describe why it happens because it's very, very complicated.
我们不打算解释为什么会这样，因为它非常非常复杂。

166
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:03,400
And you can look it up on our site.
你可以在我们的网站上查一下。

167
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:05,720
But we're going to describe how to use it.
但我们要解释如何使用它。

168
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:06,720
That's the most important.
那是最重要的。

169
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:12,600
So we can say, for example, Marco, if I were you, I would dye my hair red.
所以，我们可以说，例如，Marco，“if I were you, I would dye my hair red”。

170
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:13,600
Why?
为什么？

171
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:14,600
I don't know.
我不知道。

172
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:15,600
I think it would look cool.
我觉得那样会看起来很酷。

173
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:16,680
I don't think so.
我不这么认为。

174
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:19,320
So if I were you, I would.
所以，“if I were you, I would”。

175
00:08:19,320 --> 00:08:22,000
Or if you were me, what would you do?
或者“if you were me, what would you do？”

176
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,000
Exactly.
没错。

177
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,680
So we always use it like this, right?
所以，我们总是这样用，对吧？

178
00:08:24,680 --> 00:08:29,200
If you're going to use this conditional, always use were for the subject.
如果你要用这个条件句，主语后面总是用“were”。

179
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:30,200
Never was.
永远不要用“was”。

180
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:31,200
Right.
对。

181
00:08:31,200 --> 00:08:32,200
So you can tell.
所以，你可以看出来。

182
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:33,200
This is a very, very big grammar issue.
这是一个非常非常大的语法问题。

183
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:36,040
A lot of English speakers make this mistake.
很多英语母语者都会犯这个错误。

184
00:08:36,040 --> 00:08:37,720
Yes, very many.
是的，非常多。

185
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:41,520
But now you know that you shouldn't make this mistake and you can speak properly.
但现在你知道你不应该犯这个错误，你可以说得更规范。

186
00:08:41,520 --> 00:08:47,560
All right, so now that we've seen these semi-unreal situations, let's move on to something that's
好了，现在我们看完了这些半真实的情况，让我们继续讨论一些

187
00:08:47,560 --> 00:08:50,680
a little bit more probable, that it may happen.
更可能发生、可能会发生的事情。

188
00:08:50,680 --> 00:08:51,680
Right.
对。

189
00:08:51,680 --> 00:08:56,400
So we've got these situations that are common or likely.
所以，我们有这些常见或可能的情况。

190
00:08:56,400 --> 00:09:00,520
For example, in this lesson we hear, I will go with you for sure.
例如，在这节课中，我们听到“I will go with you for sure”。

191
00:09:00,520 --> 00:09:05,100
So this is, if you buy me a ticket to travel, of course I will go with you.
所以，这是“if you buy me a ticket to travel, of course I will go with you”。

192
00:09:05,100 --> 00:09:10,600
So if you buy, this is in the present tense, if you buy, then I will.
所以，“if you buy”，这是现在时态，“if you buy, then I will”。

193
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:11,600
Right.
对。

194
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:12,600
Right.
对。

195
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:13,600
So now you notice the difference.
所以，现在你注意到区别了。

196
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:17,840
The verb is in the present and then we use, instead of would, we use will.
动词是现在时，然后我们不用“would”，而用“will”。

197
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:25,360
So again, I can say, if it rains tomorrow, I will stay home and watch TV all day.
所以，我再说一遍，“if it rains tomorrow, I will stay home and watch TV all day”。

198
00:09:25,360 --> 00:09:27,800
Okay, so think about this.
好的，想想这个。

199
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:32,400
Before we talked about going to desert islands, now we're talking about rain and the weather.
之前我们谈论去荒岛，现在我们谈论下雨和天气。

200
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:33,760
They're very, very different.
它们非常非常不同。

201
00:09:33,760 --> 00:09:35,440
The rain is, you know, it's very common.
这雨吧，你知道，挺常见的。

202
00:09:35,440 --> 00:09:40,420
So we can say, if it rains tomorrow, I will need an umbrella.
所以我们可以说，如果明天下雨，我就需要一把伞。

203
00:09:40,420 --> 00:09:41,420
What about this?
那这个呢？

204
00:09:41,420 --> 00:09:43,640
If we have lunch tomorrow, what will we eat?
如果我们明天一起吃午饭，我们会吃什么？

205
00:09:43,640 --> 00:09:46,560
Okay, so we have lunch pretty much every day, right?
好吧，我们几乎每天都一起吃午饭，对吧？

206
00:09:46,560 --> 00:09:47,560
Yeah, pretty much.
是啊，差不多。

207
00:09:47,560 --> 00:09:50,760
So again, it's a situation that is very probable.
所以再说一次，这是一个非常可能发生的情况。

208
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:57,280
So if we have lunch tomorrow, we will probably eat, I don't know, pasta, I think.
所以如果我们明天一起吃午饭，我们可能会吃，嗯，我想是意大利面吧。

209
00:09:57,280 --> 00:09:58,280
I'm feeling like pasta.
我想吃意大利面。

210
00:09:58,280 --> 00:09:59,280
Pasta, noodles.
意大利面，面条。

211
00:09:59,280 --> 00:10:00,280
Yeah.
嗯。

212
00:10:00,280 --> 00:10:03,840
All right, so Marco, let's take another listen to some of these phrases and try and figure
好了，马可，我们再听一遍这些短语，试着在听的时候分辨一下，这是哪种条件句，第一类还是第二类。

213
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:10,400
out while you're listening, which kind of conditional it is, first or the second.


214
00:10:10,400 --> 00:10:11,400
Example one.
例子一。

215
00:10:11,400 --> 00:10:16,880
If it's sunny today, we will go to the park.
如果今天天气晴朗，我们就去公园。

216
00:10:16,880 --> 00:10:17,880
Example two.
例子二。

217
00:10:17,880 --> 00:10:22,320
I would get a divorce if I were you.
如果我是你，我会离婚。

218
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:23,320
Example three.
例子三。

219
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:29,000
Mary will be very sad if Joe leaves.
如果乔离开，玛丽会非常难过。

220
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:32,160
Example four.
例子四。

221
00:10:32,160 --> 00:10:37,000
We wouldn't be so late if Nick drove faster.
如果尼克开快一点，我们就不会这么晚了。

222
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,000
Very good.
非常好。

223
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:42,240
So we have two different examples and the first conditional is the one that we mentioned
所以我们有两个不同的例子，第一条件句是我们提到的非常可能发生的情况，第二条件句是不太可能发生的情况。

224
00:10:42,240 --> 00:10:47,260
is very probable and the second conditional is the one that's not so probable.


225
00:10:47,260 --> 00:10:48,720
So they're very easy to distinguish.
它们很容易区分。

226
00:10:48,720 --> 00:10:52,760
You don't really need to know the names, just know how to use them, right?
你其实不需要知道名字，只要知道怎么用就行，对吧？

227
00:10:52,760 --> 00:10:53,760
Exactly.
没错。

228
00:10:53,760 --> 00:10:57,600
And so just remember, if you were me, what would you do?
所以只要记住，如果你是我，你会怎么做？

229
00:10:57,600 --> 00:11:01,040
We've got these kind of pairs, these words that go together.
我们有这些成对的词，这些搭配在一起的词。

230
00:11:01,040 --> 00:11:02,720
And the other one is more common.
另一个更常见。

231
00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:06,280
If it rains tomorrow, I will bring an umbrella.
如果明天下雨，我会带伞。

232
00:11:06,280 --> 00:11:07,280
Perfect.
完美。

233
00:11:07,280 --> 00:11:12,280
So why don't we listen to this dialogue for the last time just to kind of reinforce everything
那我们最后再听一遍这段对话，巩固一下所有内容，然后我们再回来多聊一会儿。

234
00:11:12,280 --> 00:11:21,520
and then we'll come back and talk a little bit more.


235
00:11:21,520 --> 00:11:23,020
Okay next question.
好了，下一个问题。

236
00:11:23,020 --> 00:11:25,680
If Eric asked you out on a date, what would you say?
如果埃里克约你出去，你会怎么说？

237
